<scriptment id="96000" point="last_drink" localizationstatus="original" fictionaldate="2011-11-28" status="final">
	<part>
		<narration>All around the bar table look at their hard, hard drinks.</narration>
		<line id="1000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">The Sega Corporation will go bankrupt on December 12, 2011.</line>
		<narration><comment>Mark it in the calendar.</comment>Yuki downs another. She sighs.</narration>
		<line id="2000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">I can't even keep a multinational corporation afloat.</line>
		<narration>Hanako slams a glass.</narration>
		<line id="3000" speaker="hanako" voicelang="ja">You're gonna cry about that, too?</line>
		<line id="4000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">If I was halfway decent, I could beat The Group.</line>
		<line id="5000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">Maybe I'm not so good at this "life" thing.</line>
		<line id="6000" speaker="takuya" voicelang="ja">"Good at?" Life is not a game.</line>
		<line id="7000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">Life is not A Game.</line>
		<line id="8000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">Life is The Game.</line>
	</part>
</scriptment>